ws that courtrooms served the colonial Virginia frontier well in enforcing credit contracts Read More   Secretary to BOV  Assistant to Superintendent Named LEXINGTON  Va  Aug  14  2015   Retired Air Force Lt  Col  Sean Harrington  94 has been named secretary to the Board of Visitors and executive assistant to the superintendent at Virginia Military Institute  He began his duties Aug  1  Col  Jeff Curtis  79  former executive assistant  retired Friday  Aug  7  Curtis first came to VMI as chief of staff in July 2009 and became executive assistant in 2013 Read More   VMI Professor to Discuss Amazon River Fish LEXINGTON  Va  Aug  13  2015   Virginia Military Institute associate professor Lt  Col  Pieter deHart will be heard on the public radio show With Good Reason the week of Aug  15  In the episode   It s a Jungle Out There  deHart will talk about his efforts to discover which organisms are at the base of the food web in Brazil s Rio Negro  where all of the fish in the acidic  black water appear to be carnivores Read More   Taps   Gen  Sam S  Walker  45LEXINGTON  Va  Aug  11  2015   Retired U S  Army Gen  Sam Sims Walker  45  11th superintendent of VMI  died Saturday  Aug  8  2015 Read More   Getting Her Hands Dirty LEXINGTON  Va  July 27  2015   Cadet Allison Partin  17 interned this summer at the Buena Vista Wastewater Treatment Plant  where she learned about water quality   and the strange items people flush down the toilet Read More   On Social Media  Movements Start Themselves LEXINGTON  Va  July 23  2015  Cadet Matt Armentrout  16 has spent the summer studying the power of social media to instigate movements for change such as the Occupy protests Read More   Cadet Intern Takes on Trail Safety Issues LEXINGTON  Va  July 20  2015   Josh Pike  17  a civil engineering major  is working this summer to make the VMI owned Chessie Nature Trail a safer and more enjoyable place for visitors Read More    Money  Ranks VMI Third in Virginia LEXINGTON  Va  July 14  2015   Vir